The paper deals with algorithms for graph partitioning, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of priority task-scheduling framework suggests a focus on parallel computing (cs.CC), and the discussion of lower bounds and their impact on solution speed suggests a focus on optimization and machine learning (cs.LG).
